description:
&lt;p&gt;Not all Hero’s wear capes. Now more than ever, being a #NHSHero is something to be proud about. We’re currently looking for experienced Administrators to join the County Healthy Together Administration Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vacancies&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have three exciting opportunities to join our established team:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1. 30 Hours, Permanent Contract, Monday – Friday, 9.00 – 3.00pm, Based at Narborough Health Centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;2. 22.5 Hours, Permanent Contact, Wednesday – Friday, 9.00 – 5.00pm, Based at Narborough Health Centre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;3. 30 Hours, 9 - 12 Month Fixed Term Contact (Maternity Leave Cover), Monday – Friday, 9.30 – 3.30pm, Based at Charnwood Mill.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note the working pattern and hours are currently fixed due to service need.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be joining a well-established admin team who provide support for the 0-19 clinical team who deliver Public Health nursing across Leicestershire and Rutland. The team is made up of 10 other Administrators and 3 Senior Administrators and are based in various LPT sites across Leicestershire and Rutland.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will receive an individual training package and ongoing support from dedicated Senior Administrators and ongoing regular supervision with the Team Leader.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will involve:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing conflicting demands and effectively prioritising workload&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Booking various appointments for patients within specific timescales/Key Performance Indicators&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintaining Electronic Patient Records&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow Standard Operating Procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Making and taking phone calls from Patients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scanning documents onto Patient Records&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Using Microsoft Office Packages; Excel, Word, Outlook&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working as part of an effective team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Being adaptable and positive to change&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Previous applicants to recent healthy together vacancies – Need Not Apply.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Next Steps&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you like what you’ve read, please apply and Gemma Billson will be in touch. If you’d like to have an informal conversation, please contact 07557173365.&lt;/p&gt;
